parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear hatch latch can cause the hatch to open while driving, resulting in loss of cargo and potentially causing accidents or injuries. In some cases, it can also trap passengers inside the vehicle.
symptoms: The rear hatch latch does not close properly
the latch makes a rattling noise
the screw comes loose and is lost.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking of the door lock can prevent passengers from exiting the vehicle, potentially causing injuries or fatalities in emergency situations.
symptoms: not allowing passengers to exit the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motor mount can cause damage to the oil pan and other surrounding components, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents due to loss of control.
symptoms: Fluid leaking from underneath the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door hinges can cause doors to separate from the vehicle, leading to accidents or injuries, and potentially causing damage to the vehicle or other objects.
symptoms: doors locking or unlocking upon being closed

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the liftgate or hatch can cause accidents or injuries, and potentially causing damage to the vehicle or other objects.
symptoms: Liftgate or hatch opening by itself while driving
liftgate or hatch falling off hinges
liftgate or hatch not staying up
injuries to persons opening the door.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine harmonic imbalance can cause failure of the air conditioner and alternator, leading to loss of power and potentially stranding the driver.
Failure of the emission control system can lead to increased emissions, potentially causing environmental harm and negatively impacting vehicle performance.
Failure of the PCV valve can cause engine problems, including oil leaks and premature wear on engine components.
Failure of engine components, such as cam bolts, camshafts, and cylinder heads, can cause premature wear, engine lockup, and potentially lead to engine failure.
Failure of engine mounts can cause engine vibration, noise, and potentially lead to engine damage.
symptoms: engine movement during acceleration or braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the CV joint can cause loss of vehicle control, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Clicking or clunking noise from the front wheels

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine fires can cause significant damage to the vehicle and potentially harm occupants.
symptoms: smoke or flames visible from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Loss of power can cause loss of vehicle control, potentially leading to accidents.
Excessive oil consumption and leaks can cause engine damage, premature wear, and potentially lead to engine failure.
symptoms: smoke or noise from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the MAP sensor can cause poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially lead to engine damage.
